	(-3001001,'<Guard-Master Lesia gives you a quick, demeaning glance and says with a bore:>\r\n\r\nA new recruit? How exiting... Let me see if you\'re in my papers, although judging by your rugged clothes I doubt it...\r\n\r\n<Lesia searches through his papers, flipping page after page. His eyes only half open, his finger tracing his gaze upon the old parchment.>\r\n\r\n<Reaching your name Lesia\'s eyes begin to widen. He looks up; surprise written all over him.>\r\n\r\nBut, surely... It cannot be...',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'GOSSIP_GM_LESIA_1'),
	(-3001002,'<Lesia stands quiet for a moment, lost in his own thought, giving no apparent sign that he heard your question.>\r\n\r\n<Then, seemingly having made up his mind, he clears his throat and says:>\r\n\r\nYes, there\'s only one way to find out...\r\n\r\n<Guard-Master Lesia eyes you seriously, as if what he is about to say carries great significance.>\r\n\r\nAccording to my papers, you are not meant for this place. The blood in your veins, the heritage you carry, is far too important to be spilt in these surroundings.\r\n\r\n<Lesia looks around, eyes filled with unquestionable disgust for the insignificance of the place in which he was stationed.>\r\n\r\nI can, however, grant you a way out of here. But, beware; it\'s very dangerous, and if you are anyone less than I think you are, then certain death is the only outcome. But if you are who my papers say, then glory and riches is surely in store for you.\r\n\r\nHow about it, recruit?\r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'GOSSIP_GM_LESIA_2'),
	(-3001000,'<Guard-Master Lesia looks up at you with a bored glance, then, seemingly uninterested of your appearance, looks back down to the bunch of parchments in his hands.>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'GOSSIP_GM_LESIA_STD'),
	(-3001003,'<Guard-Master Lesia, being pleased with himself, smiles broadly.>\r\n\r\nIt appears I was right...\r\n\r\nSo, anyway, how do you like that gear I got for you? It\'s just a mixture of items that were lingering in my backpack, but still... Might come in handy.\r\n\r\nNo, no, there\'s no need to thank me. Just try not to forget about old Lesia while you conquer Azeroth.\r\n\r\n<Lesia chuckles approvingly.>\r\n\r\nNow, off you go on some epic adventure.\r\n\r\n<As he\'s about to turn around, Lesia looks back at you, realising something:>\r\n\r\nRight, I know of a way to get to the Dark Portal, which seems an appropriate destination for a soldier of your statue; shall I make the arrangements?',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'GOSSIP_GM_LESIA_3'),
